    'SIADH is euvolemic hyponatremia from inappropriate ADH secretion (small cell lung cancer is a classic ectopic source). Despite a low serum osmolality that should shut off ADH, the urine remains inappropriately concentrated (urine osmolality high, typically over 100 and often several hundred mOsm/kg). Central DI is the opposite: ADH deficiency yields dilute urine and hypernatremia. The discriminator is the urine osmolality relative to the serum osmolality; the kidney reveals the ADH state.',
