    'Acute promyelocytic leukemia (AML M3) carries the t(15;17) PML-RARA fusion that blocks myeloid differentiation at the promyelocyte stage; Auer rods and DIC are classic, and DIC is the leading early killer. All-trans retinoic acid binds RARA to force terminal differentiation of the malignant promyelocytes and rapidly improves the coagulopathy; arsenic trioxide is added. ATRA should be started as soon as APL is suspected. The discriminator: t(15;17) means ATRA.',
