    'Reed-Sternberg cells are large binucleate (or bilobed) cells with prominent eosinophilic nucleoli giving an owl-eye look; they are CD15+ and CD30+ and are the diagnostic hallmark of Hodgkin lymphoma, typically arising on a reactive inflammatory background and presenting with contiguous lymphadenopathy and B symptoms in a young adult. The discriminator: owl-eye binucleate Reed-Sternberg cells define Hodgkin and are absent in non-Hodgkin lymphomas.',
